      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean i get the \"consult an attorney\" thing but that's just what they want u to do so they can keep control. if u look at the actual math of sovereignty, a government only has power if they can exert physical force. they can't seize a private key or a decentralized node. if i'm living my life through these protocols, isn't it basically just a form of seizure for them to demand a cut of my digital existence? it feels like they're overstepping their constitutional bounds by trying to tax a non-physical entity.",
